# Assets Loans And Receivables Insurance Recoveries Reinsurance Amount

## identifier
de12999

## type
float

## definition
This is the value, as at the relevant date, for reinsurance recoverables, being amounts due to the reporting insurer under a reinsurance arrangement that arise from the recognition of outstanding claims liability (OCL). This item is to be determined in accordance with relevant accounting standard.

## syntax
### xbrl
- balance=debit
- name=Assets.LoansAndReceivables.InsuranceRecoveriesReinsurance.Amount
- classification=baf/bafpo/bafpo5.02.10
- period=instant
